The Federal Government has offered for subscription by auction, N135 billion bonds in its Aug. 23 auction, according to the Debt Management Office (DMO). The offering circular obtained from the DMOâ€™s website indicates that it would sell N35 billion of a bond, to mature in July, 2021, at 14.50 per cent. It would also sell N50 billion at 16.28 per cent to mature in March 2027, while another N50 billion of paper would be sold at 16.24 per cent, to mature in April 2037. All the bonds on offer are reopening of previous issues, the circular said. Nigeria issues sovereign bonds monthly to support the local bond market. It also created a benchmark for corporate issuance to fund its budget deficit.